Keeps the patients moving through.

06:01.930 --> 06:04.298
- Ten minutes?
- Ten minutes.

06:04.332 --> 06:06.000
I don't think that's possible because...

06:06.034 --> 06:08.168
Rumination disorder,
six and a half minutes.

06:08.203 --> 06:11.872
<i>♪ </i>

06:11.906 --> 06:13.092
Ten minutes it is.

06:13.127 --> 06:15.909
<i>♪ </i>

06:15.944 --> 06:17.711
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

06:18.580 --> 06:21.287
Ah, just the man I wanted to see.

06:21.322 --> 06:24.018
Really? I haven't implemented
any policies that even slightly

06:24.052 --> 06:26.887
resemble socialism today,
but it is still early.

06:26.921 --> 06:29.356
- What is that god-awful smell?
- It's breakfast.

06:29.391 --> 06:31.992
It's a bagel, uh,
cream cheese, lox, capers,

06:32.027 --> 06:33.994
blended to perfection
and about all my throat

06:34.029 --> 06:35.529
- can handle right now.
- Max.

06:35.563 --> 06:37.097
- Yeah.
- I need you to help me.

06:37.132 --> 06:39.166
Yeah, well, how can I, uh, you know...

06:39.200 --> 06:41.435
SO, Karen Brantley is out of control.

06:41.469 --> 06:43.203
- The new chair of the board?
- Yep.

06:43.238 --> 06:45.205
She's just another billionaire
who thinks that her

06:45.240 --> 06:48.442
business acumen makes her
an expert on healthcare.

06:48.476 --> 06:50.611
Well, who better to make
decisions for a public hospital

06:50.645 --> 06:52.179
than somebody who will
never step foot in one?

06:52.213 --> 06:54.014
Right, but she's trying to push the board

06:54.049 --> 06:56.450
into restructuring New
Amsterdam into a profit center.

06:56.484 --> 06:58.218
Ah, yeah, kinda goes against our whole

06:58.253 --> 06:59.953
- being a patient center.
- Exactly.

06:59.988 --> 07:01.088
And I'm the only one on
the board who's willing

07:01.122 --> 07:02.556
to stand up to her.

07:02.590 --> 07:05.092
Well, I would have your back
if I was on the board.

07:05.126 --> 07:07.461
- Max, you are on the board.
- I am?

07:07.495 --> 07:09.229
You are, you just never attend meetings.

07:09.264 --> 07:10.864
So I need you to talk to Karen Brantley.

07:10.899 --> 07:12.433
I need you to give her the full Max.

07:12.467 --> 07:15.869
- Just turn this around.
- Yeah, consider it turned.

07:15.904 --> 07:17.204
- Done.
- Okay.

07:17.238 --> 07:19.422
- Yeah.
- Don't take the smoothie.

07:27.315 --> 07:31.185
Miss? It's kinda cold out here.

07:31.920 --> 07:33.454
Do you wanna come inside the hospital?

07:35.090 --> 07:36.156
Miss?

07:36.191 --> 07:39.159
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

07:39.194 --> 07:41.128
<i>♪ </i>

07:41.162 --> 07:42.563
Excuse me.

07:42.597 --> 07:43.931
<i>♪ </i>

07:43.965 --> 07:45.299
Excuse me!

07:45.333 --> 07:50.270
<i>♪ </i>

07:50.305 --> 07:51.372
[GASPS]

07:53.007 --> 07:54.608
Found down, unresponsive,
pinpoint pupils,

07:54.642 --> 07:56.076
respiratory rate of five.

07:56.111 --> 07:57.177
Looks like an opioid overdose.

07:57.212 --> 07:58.512
I need an intranasal Narcan.

07:58.546 --> 08:00.914
<i>♪ </i>

08:00.949 --> 08:02.616
Rashes and blisters all over.
Are you on it?

08:02.650 --> 08:04.151
Get a tube in.

08:04.185 --> 08:05.486
[GASPS]

08:05.520 --> 08:07.321
[COUGHING]

08:07.355 --> 08:08.589
Where am I?

08:08.623 --> 08:10.257
- My bag. Where's my bag?
- Whoa.

08:10.291 --> 08:12.192
She's probably looking for her stash.

08:12.227 --> 08:13.660
What did you do with my bag?
What did you do with my bag?!

08:13.695 --> 08:15.295
- Calm down.
- I have to get out of here!

08:15.330 --> 08:17.264
- Ma'am, ma'am, ma'am!
- No, I need my bag!

08:17.298 --> 08:18.648
Please!

08:19.467 --> 08:20.634
Please.

08:20.668 --> 08:27.741
<i>♪ </i>

08:29.344 --> 08:32.312
[BABY CRYING]

08:32.347 --> 08:39.419
<i>♪ </i>

08:42.477 --> 08:44.844
[BABY CRYING]

08:45.154 --> 08:47.188
She can't be more than a week old.

08:47.222 --> 08:50.625
- Neonatal Abstinence Syndrome.
- How bad?

08:50.659 --> 08:52.916
Finnegan score is through the roof.

08:52.941 --> 08:54.809
Good thing you found her when you did.

08:54.843 --> 08:57.078
She wouldn't have lasted more
than an hour out there.

08:57.112 --> 08:58.279
Is she gonna be okay?

08:58.313 --> 09:00.147
[BABY CRYING]

09:00.182 --> 09:02.583
Go and talk to the mother.
I'll take it from here.

09:02.618 --> 09:05.586
[BABY CRYING]

09:05.621 --> 09:08.589
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

09:08.624 --> 09:10.791
<i>♪ </i>

09:10.826 --> 09:14.795
Wendy, your baby is suffering
from opioid withdrawal.

09:14.830 --> 09:17.164
<i>♪ </i>

09:17.199 --> 09:18.933
You're gonna be feeling it soon, too.

09:18.967 --> 09:21.235
<i>♪ </i>

09:21.270 --> 09:23.170
Is there someone that we
can call for you?

09:23.205 --> 09:25.072
<i>♪ </i>

09:25.107 --> 09:26.807
And your baby?

09:26.842 --> 09:29.677
<i>♪ </i>

09:29.711 --> 09:31.245
Are you sure? Hm.

09:31.280 --> 09:38.319
<i>♪ </i>

09:39.187 --> 09:40.788
I didn't mean to hurt her.

09:40.822 --> 09:44.792
<i>♪ </i>

09:44.826 --> 09:46.193
I just couldn't...

09:46.228 --> 09:49.997
<i>♪ </i>

09:50.032 --> 09:52.333
I couldn't quit.

09:52.367 --> 09:53.768
I tried.

09:53.802 --> 09:59.840
<i>♪ </i>

09:59.875 --> 10:01.208
I swear I tried.

10:01.243 --> 10:04.178
<i>♪ </i>

10:04.212 --> 10:08.716
[BABY CRYING]

10:08.750 --> 10:09.984
What's her name?

10:10.018 --> 10:12.219
<i>♪ </i>

10:12.254 --> 10:13.721
I never gave her one.

10:13.755 --> 10:18.359
<i>♪ </i>

10:18.393 --> 10:20.061
Another vet.

10:20.095 --> 10:22.830
Yeah, Alex Demos was lucky
surviving a six story fall.

10:22.864 --> 10:25.066
Uh-huh, and appears to be heavily sedated

10:25.100 --> 10:26.801
for surgical transport.

10:26.835 --> 10:28.969
Bit of an obstacle when
it comes to talk therapy.

10:29.004 --> 10:31.072
So, what's going on?
What am I doing here?

10:31.106 --> 10:32.840
We need answers he can't give.

10:32.874 --> 10:35.710
We found these on him and this
is not his first rodeo.

10:35.744 --> 10:36.911
Yeah.

10:36.945 --> 10:38.846
See, these fractures are from today,

10:38.880 --> 10:41.015
but these are all healed fractures.

10:41.049 --> 10:42.316
Oh, yeah.

10:42.351 --> 10:45.152
He's undergone massive, repeated trauma.

10:45.187 --> 10:46.687
That is some rodeo.

10:46.722 --> 10:48.656
This guy's intent on hurting himself,

10:48.690 --> 10:51.258
and he's gonna keep trying
unless we can help him.

10:51.293 --> 10:53.160
Yeah, okay.

10:53.195 --> 10:55.196
All right, let me reach out
to my contacts at the VA.

10:55.230 --> 10:56.397
See what I can find out.

10:56.431 --> 10:57.398
Okay.

10:57.432 --> 11:00.334
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

11:00.369 --> 11:03.604
Headaches started around
the time my in-laws moved in.

11:03.638 --> 11:04.872
Maybe it's psychosomatic.

11:04.906 --> 11:06.774
But joint pain is not.

11:06.808 --> 11:08.709
Hi, hon. You doing okay?

11:08.744 --> 11:09.844
Can I get you anything?

11:09.878 --> 11:11.379
I'm fine, Irene.

11:11.413 --> 11:14.215
I don't think you're supposed
to be back here.

11:14.249 --> 11:16.350
Oh, sorry.

11:16.385 --> 11:18.052
I'm around if you need me.

11:18.086 --> 11:21.055
<i>[LIGHT PERCUSSIVE MUSIC]</i>

11:21.089 --> 11:22.356
<i>♪ </i>

11:48.250 --> 11:55.055
<i>♪ </i>

11:55.090 --> 11:57.458
Oh, yes.

11:57.492 --> 11:58.959
One second, please.

11:58.994 --> 12:02.129
<i>♪ </i>

12:02.164 --> 12:04.331
Sorry, I need more time.

12:04.366 --> 12:06.967
You've had ten minutes.

12:07.002 --> 12:10.004
But Mrs. Laghari's tests
are inconclusive.

12:10.038 --> 12:12.406
I need a more detailed medical history.

12:12.441 --> 12:14.842
<i>♪ </i>

12:14.876 --> 12:18.145
So, ten more minutes, please.

12:18.180 --> 12:21.115
In the spirit of calm efficiency.

12:21.149 --> 12:23.350
<i>♪ </i>

12:23.385 --> 12:24.952
- Ten more minutes.
- Thank you.

12:24.986 --> 12:25.953
But not more.

12:25.987 --> 12:29.323
<i>♪ </i>

12:29.357 --> 12:30.656
Someone page me?

12:30.690 --> 12:32.159
- Yeah, jumper in trauma one.
- Uh-huh.

12:32.194 --> 12:34.195
And heads up. Night shift rules today.

12:34.229 --> 12:36.096
- Candelario's in charge.
- Where's Bloom?

12:36.131 --> 12:37.298
Vacation.

12:37.332 --> 12:39.200
- Bloom's on vacation?
- I know.

12:39.234 --> 12:42.036
I hope it's not a sign of the apocalypse.

12:42.070 --> 12:43.704
Sort of sudden.

12:43.738 --> 12:45.139
- She say where she was going?
- Nope.

12:45.173 --> 12:46.841
Nor is it any of my concern.

12:46.875 --> 12:48.876
Neither is the color
of her favorite swimsuit

12:48.910 --> 12:51.212
or whether she packed
an appropriate sunscreen.

12:51.246 --> 12:54.114
What is my concern is my patients.

12:54.149 --> 12:55.783
Here in the ED.

12:55.817 --> 12:57.318
[MONITORS BEEPING]

12:57.352 --> 12:58.452
Was just curious.

12:58.487 --> 13:02.189
<i>♪ </i>

13:02.224 --> 13:04.859
All I know is that Max asked
me to take her off the schedule

13:04.893 --> 13:06.494
for the next four weeks.

13:06.528 --> 13:08.996
Four weeks?

13:09.030 --> 13:10.331
"Out of the night that covers me,

13:10.365 --> 13:12.500
"black as the pit from pole to pole,

13:12.534 --> 13:15.336
- I thank whatever gods may be..."
