14:03.151 --> 14:05.886
Uh, see, they use these,
um, croissants instead

14:05.921 --> 14:07.705
of hot dog buns, so...

14:08.557 --> 14:10.858
- Nice touch. [CHUCKLES]
- Yeah.

14:10.892 --> 14:12.393
Um...

14:12.427 --> 14:13.861
You're not joining me?

14:13.895 --> 14:16.297
Mmm, drinking mine, actually.

14:16.331 --> 14:18.866
It's, uh, chili cheese fries
and, uh... and a little bit

14:18.900 --> 14:21.135
of chocolate shake. It's, uh, not bad.

14:21.169 --> 14:22.236
[CHUCKLES]

14:23.505 --> 14:26.974
So, I thought maybe we should
discuss some of your proposed,

14:27.008 --> 14:28.542
uh, changes for New Amsterdam.

14:28.577 --> 14:31.145
I'm going to assume you
already talked with Dean Fulton

14:31.179 --> 14:32.613
so let me save you
the trouble of delivering

14:32.647 --> 14:34.481
the rousing speech you no doubt prepared.

14:34.516 --> 14:35.883
[CHUCKLES]

14:35.917 --> 14:36.984
I don't know if I'd say rousing.

14:37.018 --> 14:39.219
It was stirring, maybe, but...

14:39.254 --> 14:41.088
I believe we can turn New Amsterdam

14:41.122 --> 14:44.224
into a profit center while
still putting patients first.

14:45.527 --> 14:46.894
You do?

14:47.862 --> 14:50.130
The Dean sees everything
as black or white,

14:50.165 --> 14:51.966
good or bad.

14:52.000 --> 14:55.169
Which is why the board thinks
it's time for a different Dean.

14:56.211 --> 14:57.504
They what?

14:57.539 --> 15:00.074
The board's calling a vote
to terminate Fulton's contract.

15:00.108 --> 15:02.009
Tonight's meeting.

15:02.760 --> 15:04.178
Well...

15:04.613 --> 15:07.147
Wow, when were you planning
on telling Dean Fulton this?

15:07.182 --> 15:08.516
Tonight.

15:09.184 --> 15:11.318
Look, Max, I like you.

15:11.353 --> 15:13.187
You think outside the box.

15:13.221 --> 15:15.289
Renting an apartment
for that homeless person,

15:15.323 --> 15:17.591
reallocating obsolete resources

15:17.626 --> 15:19.259
to service the Sheepshead Bay area,

15:19.294 --> 15:21.028
you're actually making money.

15:21.062 --> 15:22.529
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

15:22.564 --> 15:25.532
- And helping people.
- See?

15:25.567 --> 15:29.536
We can do both. You, me, and a new Dean.

15:29.571 --> 15:30.938
<i>♪ </i>

15:30.972 --> 15:32.172
What do you say?

15:32.207 --> 15:34.942
<i>♪ </i>

15:34.976 --> 15:36.043
Mmm.

15:36.077 --> 15:38.879
<i>♪ </i>

15:38.913 --> 15:40.514
Miss Birdwell, it's...

15:40.548 --> 15:43.017
<i>♪ </i>

15:43.051 --> 15:45.152
Uh, where's Wendy Birdwell,
the baby's mother?

15:45.186 --> 15:47.655
Nobody told you? She left.

15:47.689 --> 15:50.290
Wait, h... her baby's still in the PIC-U.

15:50.325 --> 15:52.026
It's not her baby anymore.

15:52.060 --> 15:53.627
She Safe Haven surrendered her.

16:00.842 --> 16:03.676
[BABY CRYING]

16:03.710 --> 16:06.679
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

16:06.713 --> 16:08.514
<i>♪ </i>

16:09.685 --> 16:11.986
How's she doing?

16:12.020 --> 16:15.556
Well, she's deficient
in almost every category.

16:15.590 --> 16:18.559
And she can't keep any formula down.

16:18.593 --> 16:21.862
Jenny says that it's the worst
case of NAS she's ever seen.

16:22.298 --> 16:25.332
They think that she might
lapse into seizures.

16:25.367 --> 16:29.236
<i>♪ </i>

16:29.271 --> 16:30.738
We'll get her through it.

16:30.772 --> 16:31.806
How?

16:31.840 --> 16:34.008
<i>♪ </i>

16:34.042 --> 16:36.644
How does she get through
withdrawal and recovery

16:36.678 --> 16:38.379
without her mother?

16:38.413 --> 16:39.814
Her mother didn't even give her a name.

16:39.848 --> 16:41.549
<i>♪ </i>

16:41.583 --> 16:44.251
Maybe Safe Haven surrender
was a good choice.

16:44.286 --> 16:45.586
<i>♪ </i>

16:45.620 --> 16:48.055
No choice here is good.

16:48.577 --> 16:52.426
She's just so tiny and helpless.

16:52.461 --> 16:53.994
<i>♪ </i>

16:54.029 --> 16:56.430
Baby Doe isn't responding to treatment.

16:56.465 --> 16:57.765
To any of it?

16:57.799 --> 17:00.568
If anything, it's making her worse.

17:00.602 --> 17:02.964
Jenny, what about rooming in?

17:03.705 --> 17:05.940
It'd be worth a try,
but not without the mother.

17:05.973 --> 17:07.508
What is that?

17:07.541 --> 17:09.410
NAS babies are sensitive to stimulus

17:09.444 --> 17:11.444
and the PIC-U's a noisy place.

17:11.480 --> 17:14.749
Rooming in is skin-to-skin
contact in a calm environment

17:14.782 --> 17:16.517
to soothe the baby.

17:16.550 --> 17:17.952
But it requires constant
holding and frequent feeding

17:17.986 --> 17:19.855
from the baby's mother.

17:21.523 --> 17:23.523
I'll do it.

17:23.558 --> 17:24.925
Helen...

17:24.960 --> 17:27.962
I can't let that baby suffer anymore.

17:27.996 --> 17:31.031
[BABY CRYING]

17:35.837 --> 17:36.971
Okay, thank you.

17:37.005 --> 17:38.806
- Uh, Dr. Frome?
- Yes?

17:38.840 --> 17:40.307
Uh, I'm Alex Demos.

17:40.342 --> 17:42.977
The VA told me you found my dog tags.

17:43.011 --> 17:45.546
Yes, we did. Um...

17:46.681 --> 17:50.136
Yeah, I have them... here.

17:53.855 --> 17:57.591
Mustafa wasn't a soldier.
He was our Iraqi interpreter.

17:57.626 --> 17:59.493
Interpreters aren't, uh...
they're not part of the unit?

17:59.528 --> 18:01.996
Um, not officially, no.
But he went everywhere with us.

18:02.030 --> 18:04.064
- Mm.
- Took enemy fire with us.

18:04.099 --> 18:06.527
- Saved the whole unit more than once.
- Mmm.

18:07.312 --> 18:10.337
I mean, that's why I gave him
my dog tags when we pulled out.

18:10.372 --> 18:12.473
So he'd always know he was one of us.

18:12.507 --> 18:16.710
Mustafa's body, um,
had seen a lot of trauma.

18:17.712 --> 18:19.346
A lot of broken bones.

18:19.381 --> 18:21.582
Do you know why he would want
to harm himself?

18:21.616 --> 18:22.850
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

18:22.884 --> 18:25.152
Mustafa didn't do that.

18:25.187 --> 18:26.520
Al-Qaeda did.

18:26.555 --> 18:28.215
Ah.

18:28.623 --> 18:31.091
After we left, they found
out he'd been working for us.

18:31.126 --> 18:32.793
<i>♪ </i>

18:32.828 --> 18:35.162
They killed his father
and then they took him.

18:35.197 --> 18:37.598
Oh, my God. Okay, all right.

18:37.632 --> 18:42.536
So, after he was released,
he became suicidal.

18:42.838 --> 18:44.238
No.

18:44.263 --> 18:46.173
I mean, he was different for sure.

18:46.208 --> 18:48.319
They took something from him.

18:48.844 --> 18:52.646
I could see he was in pain,
but he was just focused

18:52.681 --> 18:56.717
on getting out of Iraq,
coming here, starting over.

18:56.751 --> 18:59.053
It took five years and all
of us writing letters

18:59.087 --> 19:01.555
of recommendation for his visa,
but we got him here.

19:01.590 --> 19:03.390
What was it like once he got here?

19:03.425 --> 19:06.060
Happy. We all went to the airport.

19:06.094 --> 19:07.862
The whole unit.

19:07.896 --> 19:10.998
And he seemed so excited
to start his new life.

19:11.032 --> 19:12.199
So then why did he jump?

19:12.234 --> 19:19.139
<i>♪ </i>

19:36.124 --> 19:38.692
How's that headache diagnosis coming?

19:38.727 --> 19:41.195
Dr. Kao gave me her ten minutes.

19:44.466 --> 19:47.434
<i>[PERCUSSIVE MUSIC]</i>

19:47.469 --> 19:52.006
<i>♪ </i>

19:57.455 --> 19:59.113
Tell me about it.

19:59.147 --> 20:01.582
<i>♪ </i>

20:05.053 --> 20:07.688
Strawberry banana. Promise.

20:07.722 --> 20:10.124
<i>[BRUCE HORNSBY'S "THE WAY IT IS"]</i>

20:10.158 --> 20:13.093
This is quite the consolation
prize for losing my job.

20:13.128 --> 20:15.195
Oh, it hasn't happened yet.

20:15.230 --> 20:16.657
Doesn't matter.

20:17.533 --> 20:19.800
Tonight is fait accompli.

20:19.834 --> 20:21.969
<i>♪ </i>

20:22.003 --> 20:24.972
You know, Max, this can't
be good for you, either.

20:25.006 --> 20:27.808
With me gone they could just
as easily bench you

20:27.842 --> 20:29.476
before your cancer does.

20:29.511 --> 20:32.613
<i>♪ Just for fun he says get a job ♪</i>

20:32.647 --> 20:35.082
Wow. I'll be damned.

20:35.116 --> 20:36.650
It's not like that.

20:36.685 --> 20:38.152
What did she offer you?

20:38.186 --> 20:39.787
Brantley said she likes
the changes I've made

20:39.821 --> 20:41.555
and she wants me to...

20:41.589 --> 20:43.090
<i>♪ Some things will never change ♪</i>

20:43.124 --> 20:44.725
Keep making them.

20:44.759 --> 20:46.293
Of course she does.

20:46.328 --> 20:48.111
The knife twists better that way.

20:48.145 --> 20:49.596
Peter...

20:49.631 --> 20:50.998
<i>♪ Ah but don't you believe them ♪</i>

20:51.032 --> 20:53.834
Okay, let me just ask you something,

20:53.868 --> 20:56.170
just out of courtesy.

20:56.204 --> 20:58.615
<i>♪ </i>

20:58.649 --> 21:00.140
Are you gonna vote with her?

21:00.175 --> 21:02.242
<i>♪ Said hey little boy you
can't go where the others go ♪</i>

21:02.277 --> 21:04.078
I'm gonna do what's best
for this hospital.

21:04.112 --> 21:07.681
<i>♪ 'Cause you don't look like they do ♪</i>

21:07.716 --> 21:10.951
Hey, let me talk to you for a second.

21:15.890 --> 21:19.927
All right, so Bloom's on vacation?

21:19.961 --> 21:21.595
- Yeah.
- [SCOFFS]

21:21.629 --> 21:23.197
That's it? She just...

21:23.231 --> 21:25.699
- She just dropped everything?
- What do you expect?

21:25.734 --> 21:28.202
She's been pulling doubles.
Doubles on top of doubles.

21:28.236 --> 21:30.204
And she wouldn't chill it
with the Adderall.

21:30.238 --> 21:31.839
It was out of control.

21:31.873 --> 21:33.707
My girl, she just needed a break.

21:33.742 --> 21:35.209
I just thank God they finally made her.

21:35.243 --> 21:38.012
Whoa, whoa. Who made her?

21:38.046 --> 21:42.783
Wait, you thought she
was actually on vacation?

21:47.188 --> 21:50.024
<i>[CALM MUSIC]</i>

21:50.058 --> 21:55.062
[COOING]

21:55.096 --> 22:02.169
<i>♪ </i>

22:12.781 --> 22:15.315
She's not crying or shaking anymore.

22:15.350 --> 22:17.194
I'd call that progress.

22:18.529 --> 22:21.355
She looks almost peaceful.

22:22.633 --> 22:23.657
Almost.

22:23.691 --> 22:30.731
<i>♪ </i>

22:32.434 --> 22:33.767
What's going on in there?

22:33.802 --> 22:36.336
<i>♪ </i>

22:36.371 --> 22:41.875
It's just, um, I was just
thinking about this morning.

22:41.910 --> 22:43.929
How nothing was normal.

22:44.946 --> 22:46.280
What's ever normal around here?

22:46.314 --> 22:48.600
My mornings usually are.

22:49.784 --> 22:51.685
But today everything was...

22:51.719 --> 22:52.953
<i>♪ </i>

22:52.987 --> 22:54.254
It was out of whack.

22:54.289 --> 22:56.190
<i>♪ </i>

22:56.224 --> 22:59.393
I was coming back from Philly.
Totally different schedule.

22:59.427 --> 23:01.028
Different subways.

23:01.062 --> 23:03.130
I didn't even come into
the hospital the same way.

23:03.164 --> 23:04.131
Hmm.

23:04.165 --> 23:05.966
<i>♪ </i>

23:06.000 --> 23:09.436
Well, you can't think about that,
the what if you hadn't found her.

23:09.471 --> 23:11.905
Well, no, it's not that.

23:11.940 --> 23:16.276
Do you ever feel like... like
the universe is trying

23:16.311 --> 23:17.778
to tell you something?

23:17.812 --> 23:19.980
<i>♪ </i>

23:20.014 --> 23:21.315
Only all the time.

23:21.349 --> 23:24.151
<i>♪ </i>

23:24.185 --> 23:26.220
You know how much I want to have a baby.

23:26.254 --> 23:28.055
<i>♪ </i>

23:28.089 --> 23:32.259
And my body hasn't exactly
been cooperating.

23:32.293 --> 23:34.428
<i>♪ </i>

23:34.462 --> 23:37.764
What if the universe brought us together?

23:37.799 --> 23:39.266
Helen...

23:39.300 --> 23:42.102
What if Zuhrah is the baby
that I was meant to have?

23:42.137 --> 23:43.937
<i>♪ </i>

23:43.972 --> 23:46.173
- Zuhrah?
- [STAMMERS]

23:46.207 --> 23:48.242
I couldn't keep calling her Baby Doe.

23:48.276 --> 23:50.037
She needed a name.

23:51.538 --> 23:52.846
She did.

23:52.881 --> 23:55.115
<i>♪ </i>

23:55.150 --> 23:56.850
I've always loved Zuhrah.

23:56.885 --> 23:58.986
<i>♪ </i>

23:59.020 --> 24:00.561
For a girl.

24:00.596 --> 24:05.359
<i>♪ </i>

24:05.393 --> 24:07.094
If I had a girl.

24:14.894 --> 24:16.961
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

24:18.418 --> 24:21.386
<i>[PERCUSSIVE MUSIC]</i>

24:21.421 --> 24:25.590
<i>♪ </i>

24:25.625 --> 24:27.292
I'm giving Dr. Kapoor my ten minutes.

24:27.326 --> 24:30.395
[OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

24:34.000 --> 24:35.033
You.

24:35.067 --> 24:41.773
<i>♪ </i>

24:41.808 --> 24:44.209
I've tried to be very patient
with you, Dr. Kapoor.

24:44.243 --> 24:47.712
Ten minute consults.
It's not that complicated.

24:47.747 --> 24:48.814
It's not enough time.

24:48.848 --> 24:50.282
Well, it is for everyone else.

24:50.316 --> 24:54.119
<i>♪ </i>

24:54.153 --> 24:58.290
My ED, my rules. Not Dr. Bloom's.

24:58.324 --> 25:01.483
For someone who does not want
to run things like Dr. Bloom,

25:02.328 --> 25:04.162
you sound exactly like her.

25:04.197 --> 25:08.233
<i>♪ </i>

25:08.267 --> 25:10.669
[SIGHS]

25:10.703 --> 25:12.304
Incoming!

25:12.338 --> 25:13.939
What the hell happened?

25:13.973 --> 25:16.308
Janitor says the Dean just collapsed
in the hall outside your office.

25:16.342 --> 25:17.809
Dean, we're gonna take good care...

25:17.844 --> 25:19.144
- I got this, I got this.
- Board meeting.

25:19.178 --> 25:20.197
I have to go to the board meeting.

25:20.231 --> 25:21.313
Don't worry about that.

25:21.347 --> 25:22.563
Just worry about getting you healthy.

25:22.597 --> 25:24.816
Give me nitro and let's
set up an IV stat.

25:24.851 --> 25:25.817
Okay? Thank you.

25:25.852 --> 25:27.986
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

25:28.020 --> 25:31.022
♪

25:31.057 --> 25:35.794
Max, we were wondering what
was taking so long.

25:35.828 --> 25:37.996
Peter had a heart attack
at New Amsterdam.

25:38.030 --> 25:39.865
- What?
- But he's gonna be all right.

25:39.899 --> 25:42.300
We expect him to make a quick
and full recovery.

25:42.335 --> 25:44.568
Oh, well, that's good to hear.

25:45.004 --> 25:46.972
Honestly, there was no better
place for him to have had it

25:47.006 --> 25:50.141
than right here surrounded
by an amazing staff

25:50.176 --> 25:53.345
who appreciate him almost as
much as the esteemed members

25:53.379 --> 25:54.745
of this board.

25:55.895 --> 25:56.929
I mean, I know I do.

25:58.050 --> 26:00.852
He never backs down
from a fight, does he?

26:02.000 --> 26:06.548
Always pushes me to do
what's best for our hospital.

26:07.093 --> 26:09.828
I can't be the medical director
I am without him.

26:11.264 --> 26:14.966
Anyway, uh, he sends along
his heartfelt thanks

26:15.001 --> 26:16.434
for your ongoing support.

26:18.068 --> 26:19.170
[DOOR OPENS]

26:19.205 --> 26:22.874
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

26:22.909 --> 26:24.376
How's your... how's your pain?

26:24.410 --> 26:26.144
How's your pain level?

26:26.178 --> 26:27.861
I've learned to live with it.

26:29.515 --> 26:32.241
Alex told me about what happened in Iraq.

26:33.286 --> 26:34.886
You've been through a lot.

26:34.921 --> 26:37.389
<i>♪ </i>

26:37.423 --> 26:41.553
Mustafa, what doesn't Alex know?

26:41.588 --> 26:43.094
Nothing.

26:43.129 --> 26:44.334
<i>♪ </i>

26:44.369 --> 26:45.830
I can't...

26:45.865 --> 26:49.798
<i>♪ </i>

26:49.832 --> 26:53.838
She can't ever find out.
She'll think it was her fault.

26:53.873 --> 26:55.941
- She's done so much for me.
- Okay, it's okay.

26:55.975 --> 26:57.208
It's all right.

26:57.243 --> 26:58.877
Anything you say, it's between us.

26:58.911 --> 27:00.879
All right? This whole thing.

27:00.913 --> 27:04.985
<i>♪ </i>

27:04.986 --> 27:08.068
I thought everything would
be better when I came here.

27:08.724 --> 27:10.696
Some things were.

27:11.093 --> 27:12.993
Alex, her family, they tried to make me

27:13.028 --> 27:14.061
feel at home.

27:14.096 --> 27:16.297
<i>♪ </i>

27:16.331 --> 27:19.033
But when I'd go out...

27:19.067 --> 27:21.202
<i>♪ </i>

27:21.236 --> 27:25.539
To the movies, the store,
to look for a job...

27:25.574 --> 27:28.042
<i>♪ </i>

27:28.076 --> 27:33.214
People just looked at me
like I was a terrorist.

27:33.248 --> 27:35.149
<i>♪ </i>

27:35.183 --> 27:37.017
Some even said it to my face.

27:37.052 --> 27:39.754
<i>♪ </i>

27:39.788 --> 27:41.589
So much for "support our troops", huh?

27:41.623 --> 27:45.326
<i>♪ </i>

27:45.360 --> 27:47.361
What about going home?
You ever think of doing that?

27:47.396 --> 27:51.932
<i>♪ </i>

27:51.967 --> 27:53.234
I can't.

27:53.268 --> 27:54.769
<i>♪ </i>

27:54.803 --> 27:55.870
There, I'm a traitor.

27:55.904 --> 27:57.838
<i>♪ </i>

27:57.873 --> 28:00.120
Because you worked for us.

28:00.709 --> 28:02.843
I thought maybe here in the city I could

28:02.878 --> 28:04.378
meet other Iraqis.

28:04.413 --> 28:07.081
<i>♪ </i>

28:07.115 --> 28:08.682
Be part of a community.

28:08.717 --> 28:11.952
<i>♪ </i>

28:11.987 --> 28:13.120
But they don't...

28:13.155 --> 28:16.957
<i>♪ </i>

28:16.992 --> 28:18.893
They weren't in the war.

28:18.927 --> 28:20.928
<i>♪ </i>

28:20.962 --> 28:22.229
They don't understand.

28:22.264 --> 28:25.232
<i>♪ </i>

28:25.267 --> 28:26.934
There's no one that I can...

28:26.968 --> 28:34.008
<i>♪ </i>

28:34.810 --> 28:36.143
I don't belong anywhere.

28:36.178 --> 28:43.250
<i>♪ </i>

28:48.323 --> 28:49.757
Alex.

28:49.791 --> 28:50.825
- Hey.
- Hi.

28:50.859 --> 28:52.092
How is he?

28:52.127 --> 28:53.828
You know, I'm... I'm not gonna lie.

28:53.862 --> 28:56.230
He's got a... a long road back from here.

28:56.264 --> 28:59.767
But the good news is I can
get him into a program here

28:59.801 --> 29:01.135
at our clinic for torture survivors,

29:01.169 --> 29:03.137
and they will be able
to provide him with a lot

29:03.171 --> 29:06.640
of the therapy he needs,
both mentally and physically.

29:07.020 --> 29:08.209
But...

29:10.111 --> 29:12.146
Oh, he's gonna need more
than that, isn't he?

29:12.848 --> 29:14.027
Yeah.

29:15.317 --> 29:16.817
Well, just tell me what I need to do.

29:17.886 --> 29:20.855
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

29:20.889 --> 29:25.359
<i>♪ </i>

29:25.393 --> 29:26.998
You finished?

29:27.829 --> 29:28.929
Hmm?

29:28.964 --> 29:31.031
<i>♪ </i>

29:31.066 --> 29:32.700
Oh.

29:32.734 --> 29:34.335
Okay.

29:34.369 --> 29:36.704
Well, you don't have
to be so bossy about it.

29:36.738 --> 29:38.005
[KISSES]

29:38.039 --> 29:39.006
[CHUCKLES]

29:39.040 --> 29:45.212
<i>♪ </i>

29:45.247 --> 29:46.447
Actually...

29:46.481 --> 29:48.816
<i>♪ </i>

29:48.850 --> 29:50.217
Be bossy.

29:50.252 --> 29:52.486
<i>♪ </i>

29:52.521 --> 29:56.123
Tell me what you want, when you want it.

29:56.157 --> 29:58.325
<i>♪ </i>

29:58.360 --> 30:00.194
You tell the world, little one.

30:00.228 --> 30:02.062
<i>♪ </i>

30:02.097 --> 30:06.367
You deserve to be heard and I
promise to hear you always.

30:06.401 --> 30:08.002
<i>♪ </i>

30:08.036 --> 30:09.069
[KISSES]

30:09.104 --> 30:14.141
<i>♪ </i>

30:14.175 --> 30:16.010
[EXHALES]

30:16.044 --> 30:21.081
<i>♪ </i>

30:21.116 --> 30:23.217
Jenny was just in to take her vitals.

30:23.251 --> 30:24.351
She told me.

30:24.386 --> 30:26.320
Treatment seems to be working.

30:26.354 --> 30:27.888
Yeah.

30:27.923 --> 30:29.890
You wouldn't believe
how much calmer she is.

30:29.925 --> 30:31.225
<i>♪ </i>

30:31.259 --> 30:33.327
She's synching to my heartbeat.

30:33.361 --> 30:35.763
<i>♪ </i>

30:35.797 --> 30:37.498
Like I'm her mom.

30:37.532 --> 30:40.401
<i>♪ </i>

30:40.435 --> 30:42.169
[CHUCKLES]

30:42.203 --> 30:44.034
Please don't look at me like that.

30:44.806 --> 30:48.242
I mean, would it really be so
crazy if I wanted to adopt her?

30:48.276 --> 30:55.316
<i>♪ </i>

30:59.054 --> 31:00.258
What?

31:02.257 --> 31:04.091
There's someone here to see the baby.

31:04.125 --> 31:05.893
<i>♪ </i>

31:05.927 --> 31:07.261
Wendy gave her up.

31:07.295 --> 31:09.263
It's not Wendy.

31:09.297 --> 31:12.099
<i>♪ </i>

31:12.133 --> 31:13.934
It's the baby's father.

31:21.437 --> 31:26.034
Do you understand that Zuhrah
was born addicted to opioids?

31:27.637 --> 31:29.204
That her mother was doing drugs

31:29.239 --> 31:31.039
while she was pregnant with her?

31:31.407 --> 31:33.442
Why didn't you get her help?

31:33.875 --> 31:35.477
I tried.

31:35.512 --> 31:36.920
She didn't listen.

31:37.614 --> 31:41.583
We broke up, like, uh, eight...
eight months ago.

31:41.618 --> 31:43.385
Moved up to Poughkeepsie.

31:43.419 --> 31:45.087
I... I didn't know about the baby.

31:46.122 --> 31:47.456
Not till three hours ago.

31:47.490 --> 31:50.492
And, uh, why did Wendy change her mind?

31:50.527 --> 31:53.996
Because this morning she didn't
want Dr. Sharpe to call anyone.

31:54.030 --> 31:56.398
Maybe she came down off the drugs.

31:56.432 --> 31:59.268
Maybe she actually realized
what she'd done.

32:04.107 --> 32:07.033
Wendy's not a... she's not a bad person.

32:07.644 --> 32:10.646
She just got caught up in all this.

32:10.680 --> 32:15.166
She had a bad fall.
Um, doctors prescribed her Oxy.

32:15.718 --> 32:16.818
She never got off it.

32:16.853 --> 32:19.821
<i>[SOMBER MUSIC]</i>

32:19.856 --> 32:22.190
<i>♪ </i>

32:22.225 --> 32:24.159
I didn't know that she was pregnant.

32:24.193 --> 32:27.262
Or I... I'd have stayed.

32:27.297 --> 32:29.014
I'd have made her get help.

32:29.465 --> 32:31.533
So that things could be better
for my daughter.

32:31.568 --> 32:33.835
<i>♪ </i>

32:33.870 --> 32:36.038
And... and I want... I want to step up.

32:36.072 --> 32:38.206
I wanna do, uh, he right thing.
I want to take her home.

32:38.241 --> 32:39.649
Yeah.

32:40.543 --> 32:41.810
It's not that easy.

32:41.844 --> 32:43.612
You got hoops?

32:43.646 --> 32:46.114
I'll jump through them.
Whatever it takes.

32:46.149 --> 32:48.350
<i>♪ </i>

32:48.384 --> 32:50.152
Yeah, okay.

32:50.186 --> 32:52.554
We'll set you up with a social
worker and get things started.

32:52.589 --> 32:54.016
Awesome. Thank you.

32:54.050 --> 32:55.457
Yeah.

32:55.491 --> 32:57.709
And, uh... and thank you, doc.

32:58.761 --> 33:01.296
For everything that you've done for her.

33:01.331 --> 33:02.831
I'll be a good dad to her.

33:02.865 --> 33:04.066
I swear.

33:04.100 --> 33:11.173
<i>♪ </i>

33:14.184 --> 33:15.410
[DOOR CLOSES]

33:15.445 --> 33:17.645
You're all set, Ms. Laghari.

33:18.114 --> 33:20.065
Thanks for listening, Dr. Kapoor.

33:29.459 --> 33:32.260
Okay, after that marathon, I gotta know.

33:32.295 --> 33:34.863
What was your final diagnosis?

33:34.897 --> 33:36.732
Lyme Disease.

33:36.766 --> 33:38.567
Lyme Disease?

33:38.601 --> 33:41.770
300,000 people get diagnosed
with Lyme Disease every year.

33:41.804 --> 33:44.373
Why did it take you all shift
to come up with that?

33:44.407 --> 33:45.874
I let her complain about her in-laws.

33:45.908 --> 33:48.443
She talked about her trips
to Minnesota to help them

33:48.478 --> 33:49.911
sell their home.

33:49.946 --> 33:53.248
I learned of their affinity
for, uh, fly fishing.

33:54.817 --> 33:57.419
Near a breeding ground for ticks.

33:58.421 --> 34:00.313
- Well done.
- Agreed.

34:01.491 --> 34:06.294
You know, when Dr. Bloom is in charge,

34:06.329 --> 34:09.130
my methods go unnoticed.

34:09.165 --> 34:13.301
But your ED ran so efficiently
today that those same methods

34:13.335 --> 34:14.786
stood out.

34:15.638 --> 34:19.141
Was there a compliment
in there somewhere, D. Kapoor?

34:19.175 --> 34:20.475
There might have been.

34:20.510 --> 34:23.478
<i>[PERCUSSIVE MUSIC]</i>

34:23.513 --> 34:25.781
<i>♪ </i>

34:25.815 --> 34:27.815
[CHUCKLES] Oh, man.

34:27.850 --> 34:30.418
You should have seen their faces.

34:30.453 --> 34:32.621
Totally bought it.

34:32.655 --> 34:34.790
I'm sure you gave them the full Max.

34:34.824 --> 34:36.925
I know you thought that
the fake heart attack thing

34:36.958 --> 34:40.495
was a little over the top,
but go big or go home, right?

34:40.530 --> 34:41.603
Right.

34:43.666 --> 34:45.300
I gotta tell you, I think you're doing

34:45.333 --> 34:47.601
amazing things at the hospital.

34:47.637 --> 34:49.170
Staff loves you.

34:49.205 --> 34:51.840
Patients thank God for you every day.

34:51.873 --> 34:54.842
And I think for me,
hiring you is the smartest

34:54.877 --> 34:58.747
thing I've done in 50 years of medicine.

34:58.781 --> 35:00.749
All right, you're gonna give
me a fake heart attack.

35:01.384 --> 35:04.186
No, but I'm... I'm just glad
I got you here

35:04.220 --> 35:05.854
- before it's too late.
- Too late?

35:05.888 --> 35:08.423
What are you... she's gonna call
any second with the terms

35:08.458 --> 35:09.691
- of your new contract. I...
- Max, Max, Max.

35:09.726 --> 35:11.551
She already called.

35:12.395 --> 35:13.962
I'm out.

35:15.298 --> 35:17.632
- No, let me... let me call her.
- Max.

35:17.667 --> 35:19.601
It's done.

35:19.635 --> 35:20.669
I'm out.

35:25.842 --> 35:27.576
I know where Bloom is.

35:29.245 --> 35:30.779
Floyd, we can't talk about that.

35:30.813 --> 35:33.381
Look, I know there
are processes in place,

35:33.416 --> 35:34.683
and I don't wanna compromise you.

35:34.717 --> 35:36.318
Okay, so then what are we doing here?

35:36.352 --> 35:37.986
Well, you're a therapist, aren't you?

35:39.589 --> 35:40.989
You could listen.

35:42.725 --> 35:44.659
Okay, yeah, I can.

35:44.694 --> 35:45.961
Come here.

35:47.864 --> 35:50.031
I am struggling here, man.

35:50.066 --> 35:53.869
I just... I can't help
but feel that I'm...

35:56.839 --> 35:59.341
You know, I thought I was her friend.

35:59.375 --> 36:01.309
But then I don't see this coming.

36:01.344 --> 36:02.852
I mean, how is that even possible?

36:04.514 --> 36:08.416
I just keep thinking that had
I asked the right questions,

36:08.451 --> 36:10.519
you know, or if I had said
the right thing and not...

36:10.553 --> 36:12.354
No, Floyd, this is not on you.

36:12.388 --> 36:14.923
Yeah, but she's my friend
and she needed my help.

36:14.957 --> 36:16.258
And I wasn't there.

36:16.292 --> 36:18.059
You need to trust the process.

36:18.094 --> 36:19.561
You need to let her have
the space she needs

36:19.595 --> 36:21.321
to work through this on her own.
That's it.

36:21.355 --> 36:23.431
This is not something that you can fix.

36:23.778 --> 36:25.011
Do you understand?

36:28.037 --> 36:29.504
Okay, good.

36:30.807 --> 36:33.775
<i>[LEON BRIDGES' "RIVER"]</i>

36:33.810 --> 36:40.849
<i>♪ </i>

36:43.986 --> 36:45.754
She's beautiful.

36:45.788 --> 36:47.722
<i>♪ </i>

36:47.757 --> 36:48.957
Do you want to hold her?

36:48.991 --> 36:50.358
<i>♪ </i>

36:50.393 --> 36:51.726
[BABY COOING]

36:51.761 --> 36:56.431
<i>♪ </i>

36:56.465 --> 36:59.734
[LAUGHING]

36:59.769 --> 37:01.999
- Hey there, little one.
<i>- ♪ Been traveling these wide roads</i>

37:02.068 --> 37:03.258
I'm your dad.

37:03.293 --> 37:04.472
<i>♪ For so long ♪</i>

37:04.507 --> 37:05.974
[LAUGHS]

37:06.008 --> 37:10.979
Uh, I hope you don't mind
if she keeps the name.

37:11.013 --> 37:13.315
Kinda suits her.

37:14.114 --> 37:15.483
Uh, what's it mean, anyway?

37:15.518 --> 37:17.986
♪ <i> Oh I wanna come here</i> ♪

37:18.020 --> 37:20.422
It means brightness.

37:20.456 --> 37:22.991
♪ <i> Every part of me</i> ♪

37:23.025 --> 37:24.893
Because that's what she'll
bring to your life.

37:24.927 --> 37:27.562
<i>♪ </i>

37:27.597 --> 37:31.399
♪ <i> And my lips aren't clean</i> ♪

37:31.434 --> 37:34.102
♪ <i> In my darkness I remember</i> ♪

37:34.136 --> 37:36.671
Hey, you up for some visitors?

37:36.706 --> 37:42.577
<i>♪ Reoccur to me surrender
to the good Lord ♪</i>

37:42.612 --> 37:45.849
<i>♪ And he'll wipe your slate clean ♪</i>

37:47.169 --> 37:49.851
♪ <i> Take me to your river</i> ♪

37:49.886 --> 37:54.522
♪ <i> I want to go</i> ♪

37:54.557 --> 37:55.590
<i>♪ </i>

37:55.625 --> 37:57.175
For you, brother.

37:58.194 --> 38:01.596
♪ <i> Oh go on</i> ♪

38:01.631 --> 38:04.799
♪ <i> Take me to your river</i> ♪

38:04.834 --> 38:09.037
♪ <i> I want to know</i> ♪

38:09.071 --> 38:10.639
You're one of us.

38:10.673 --> 38:13.008
<i>♪ </i>

38:13.042 --> 38:14.692
Always.

38:15.678 --> 38:18.113
<i>♪ Dip me in your smooth waters ♪</i>

38:18.147 --> 38:21.883
♪ <i> I go in</i> ♪

38:21.918 --> 38:24.386
♪ <i> As a man with many crimes</i> ♪

38:24.420 --> 38:26.554
♪ <i> Come up for air</i> ♪

38:26.589 --> 38:27.622
Hi.

38:27.657 --> 38:31.559
I owe you an apology.

38:31.594 --> 38:34.062
I wasn't honest with you this morning.

38:34.096 --> 38:37.399
So you are not taking me
to the greatest dinner tonight?

38:37.433 --> 38:39.000
[LAUGHS]

38:39.035 --> 38:43.004
<i>♪ But there's blood on my hands ♪</i>

38:43.039 --> 38:44.472
I love you.

38:44.507 --> 38:47.809
♪ <i> And my lips aren't clean</i> ♪

38:47.843 --> 38:49.913
- And I just, uh...
<i>- ♪ Take me to your river</i>

38:50.780 --> 38:53.014
I just can't leave
anything unsaid anymore.

38:53.049 --> 38:55.717
<i>♪ </i>

38:55.751 --> 38:58.903
You are the person I never
thought I'd find.

38:59.922 --> 39:02.365
The person I want to travel with.

39:02.959 --> 39:05.160
- Build things with.
- [LAUGHS]

39:05.194 --> 39:06.761
<i>♪ </i>

39:06.796 --> 39:08.163
Learn things from.

39:08.197 --> 39:10.699
<i>♪ </i>

39:10.733 --> 39:12.667
What do you need to learn?

39:12.702 --> 39:15.070
<i>♪ </i>

39:15.104 --> 39:16.838
How to be a better friend.

39:19.542 --> 39:23.712
Look, I, uh... I can't go
to dinner with you tonight.

39:23.746 --> 39:26.114
There's someone going
through something and...

39:26.148 --> 39:28.950
<i>♪ </i>

39:28.985 --> 39:30.452
I have to be there.

39:30.486 --> 39:32.620
<i>♪ </i>

39:32.655 --> 39:34.021
A friend?

39:34.657 --> 39:36.224
A mutual friend.

39:36.258 --> 39:38.760
<i>♪ </i>

39:38.794 --> 39:41.963
<i>♪ Wanna know, wanna know, wanna know ♪</i>

39:41.998 --> 39:43.231
Go be a good friend.

39:43.265 --> 39:45.767
<i>♪ </i>

39:45.801 --> 39:47.802
For both of us.

39:47.837 --> 39:51.706
<i>♪ </i>

39:51.741 --> 39:56.240
<i>♪ Wanna know, wanna know, wanna know ♪</i>

39:56.275 --> 40:01.483
<i>♪ Ooh oh whoa ♪</i>

40:01.517 --> 40:04.552
♪ <i> Take me to your river</i> ♪

40:04.587 --> 40:08.256
♪ <i> I wanna go</i> ♪

40:08.290 --> 40:13.561
<i>♪ </i>

40:13.596 --> 40:15.797
Are you okay? I came as soon as I could.

40:15.831 --> 40:18.166
[GRUNTS]

40:18.200 --> 40:21.569
<i>♪ </i>

40:21.604 --> 40:23.838
I need to ask you something.

40:23.873 --> 40:26.574
And you're gonna think I'm
crazy for asking you now.

40:27.877 --> 40:29.210
Just ask.

40:38.654 --> 40:41.689
I know that we haven't been
seeing each other for very long

40:41.724 --> 40:45.960
and it's way too soon to be
having this conversation

40:45.995 --> 40:50.598
but I am getting too old not
to have this conversation.

40:50.633 --> 40:52.000
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

40:52.034 --> 40:53.001
Oh.

40:53.035 --> 40:55.336
<i>♪ </i>

40:55.371 --> 40:57.005
I want to have a child.

40:57.039 --> 41:00.542
<i>♪ </i>

41:00.576 --> 41:04.712
And I need to know how you feel
about kids because I...

41:04.747 --> 41:07.670
I've been trying to find
a way to talk to you

41:07.704 --> 41:10.034
about the same thing.

41:10.686 --> 41:11.953
You have?

41:11.987 --> 41:18.693
<i>♪ </i>

41:18.727 --> 41:20.128
I love kids.

41:20.162 --> 41:22.564
<i>♪ </i>

41:22.598 --> 41:24.833
I wanted to tell you sooner.

41:24.867 --> 41:26.067
I just, um...

41:26.102 --> 41:28.069
<i>♪ </i>

41:28.104 --> 41:29.370
Had to be sure.

41:29.405 --> 41:31.306
<i>♪ </i>

41:31.340 --> 41:32.682
About?

41:33.409 --> 41:34.876
Us.

41:34.910 --> 41:41.983
<i>♪ </i>

41:55.764 --> 41:58.099
[DOOR OPENING]

41:58.134 --> 41:59.334
There's someone here to see you.

